      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I'd say Option A is the clear winner for a high-net-worth audience looking for something truly upscale. The mention of \"cobblestone streets\" and \"neoclassical architecture\" immediately evokes a sense of tradition and refinement, which is perfect for a luxury realtor's brochure. The phrase \"exclusive enclave of old-world charm\" also implies a level of exclusivity and sophistication that will likely appeal to the target audience. Option B and C are far too...common and \"urban\" for a high-end audience.",
