      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean, when you say \"the wrong kind of people\" or \"unrefined\" in relation to places with street art and diverse markets, what exactly do you mean by that? it feels like you're equating certain cultures or types of demographics with being lower class or less sophisticated. can you explain that logic a bit more clearly?",
